PERF: No unnecessary sorting.

All LS and NICDM functions now use np.partition() instead of
np.argsort(). Thus, only 1 neighbor (LS) or k neighbors (NICDM) are in
their correct positions in the matrix, which is all we need.

Reduces overall sorting complexity from O(n^2 log n) to O(n^2).
